g.text: create-local-dev-cluster Creates a local development cluster
delete-local-dev-cluster Deletes a local development cluster
docker-env Creates a dictionary to pass to ctx.run making sure the DOCKER_HOST is passed
find-charts Find chart files on a path
find-local-kube-context Find a local kubernetes contexts that have a push-able registry
find-resources Find resources across namespaces(/oc projects) running grep.
get-current-docker-host Get the current value for the DOCKER_HOST environment variable.
get-default-kube-context Get the default context in kubernetes.
get-dev-cluster-name Gets the name of the default cluster
get-git-worktrees Get a list of worktree data
git-push-and-pull-data Push, pull in the remote
helm-ocp-deploy Deploy the helm chart into a OCP cluster. We use the kubernetes context
helm-template Generates the YAML from a Helm chart
install-ctlptl Download control patrol (created local development clusters with connected registries)
install-yq Download the yq binary to convert YAML to JSON and query
kube-context-picker Shows a kubernets context picker dialog using fzf
kube-exec Shells into a pod using kubectl exec
oc-project-switcher An interactive project switcher based in fzf
pod-debug Runs a container in a pod for debugging in interactive mode
tell-application-to-quit Use osasccript in OSX to tell an application to quit
tilt-open Opens the system default browser on tilt UI
tilt-up Runs tilt up with a local kubernetes cluster
worktree Create a git worktree for reviewing a pull request. This feature is no available
worktree-editor-open Opens the editor in a worktree
worktree-list List worktrees and displays the one in use.
